HEADWORD: Libra
<hw>Li"bra</hw> <pr>(l⟦imac⟧"br⟦adot⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Libr⟦ae⟧</plw> <pr>(l⟦imac⟧"br⟦emac⟧)</pr>.</plu>
<ety>[L., a balance.]</ety> <fld>(Astron.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>The
Balance; the seventh sign in the zodiac, which the sun enters at the
autumnal equinox in September, marked thus ⟦Libra⟧ in almanacs,
etc.</def> <sd>(b )</sd> <def>A southern constellation between Virgo and
Scorpio.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

